      <p>where TP, FP, TN and FN represent the numbers of true positives, false positives, true negatives and false negatives, respectively. F1-score is used to assess the performance of the machine learning model, while MCC measures the differences between the prediction outputs and actual results [<xref rid="ref49" ref-type="bibr">49</xref>]. Additionally, we also plotted the receiver operating characteristic (ROC) and precision-recall curves, calculated the area under the ROC curves (AUROC) and the area under the precisionârecall curves to evaluate the performance of the predictors.</p>
